data.name: French Fry Burger
data.quickTastyDescription: A deliciously indulgent burger topped with crispy French fries for an extra crunch and flavor.
detailedCookingInstructions: Cook the burger patty on a grill or pan over medium heat for about 5-7 minutes on each side until fully cooked.
While the burger is cooking, prepare the French fries according to package instructions until crispy.
Toast the burger bun lightly on the grill or in a toaster.
Assemble the burger: Start with the bottom bun, place the lettuce, followed by the cooked burger patty.
Add the cheese slice on top of the patty to melt slightly.
Layer the tomato slices and crispy French fries on top of the cheese.
Drizzle ketchup and mayonnaise to your liking.
Top with the other half of the bun and serve hot.
